\\nTarget: Binary policy outcome\\n\\nAlgorithm: NLP + Gradient Boosting\\nExpec
ted Edge: 2-4% over market price\\n```\\n\\n---\\n\\n## 3. Categories to Avoid\\
n\\n### Sports (90% of Volume)\\n- **Why Avoid:** Highly efficient, dominated by
professional bettors with superior data\\n- **Edge:** Minimal — sportsbooks and 
sharp bettors already price efficiently\\n- **Exception:** Niche markets (colleg
e sports, international) may have inefficiencies\\n\\n### Entertainment (Celebri
ty, Awards)\\n- **Why Avoid:** Information is often private, leaks are unpredict
able\\n- **Edge:** Low — insider information dominates\\n- **Exception:** Market
s with objective metrics (Spotify charts, Rotten Tomatoes)\\n\\n### Long-Term Sp
eculative (Mars colonization, AGI timelines)\\n- **Why Avoid:** Too long time ho
rizon, no verifiable data sources\\n- **Edge:** None — pure speculation\\n\\n---
